## 2️⃣ CREATE WORKFLOW (Simple HTTP to DB)

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/workflows`

**Request:**
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/workflows \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "userId": "65a1234567890abcdef12345",
    "name": "Fetch and Store Orders",
    "description": "Get orders from API and save to MongoDB",
    "reactFlowData": {
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "node-1",
          "type": "ACTION_HTTP_REQUEST",
          "position": { "x": 0, "y": 0 },
          "data": {
            "label": "Fetch Orders",
            "config": {
              "url": "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts",
              "method": "GET",
              "headers": {}
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "node-2",
          "type": "DATABASE_MONGO_WRITE",
          "position": { "x": 300, "y": 0 },
          "data": {
            "label": "Save to Orders",
            "config": {
              "collection": "orders",
              "operation": "insertMany",
              "data": {}
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "edges": [
        {
          "id": "edge-1",
          "source": "node-1",
          "target": "node-2"
        }
      ],
      "viewport": { "x": 0, "y": 0, "zoom": 1 }
    },
    "triggerType": "MANUAL"
  }'
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "workflow": {
    "_id": "65a1234567890abcdef12346",
    "name": "Fetch and Store Orders",
    "status": "draft",
    "triggerType": "MANUAL",
    "webhookUrl": null
  }
}
```

---

## 3️⃣ CREATE WORKFLOW (With Webhook)

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/workflows`

**Request:**
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/workflows \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "userId": "65a1234567890abcdef12345",
    "name": "Order Processing Pipeline",
    "reactFlowData": { /* same as above */ },
    "triggerType": "WEBHOOK"
  }'
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "workflow": {
    "_id": "65a1234567890abcdef12347",
    "name": "Order Processing Pipeline",
    "status": "draft",
    "triggerType": "WEBHOOK",
    "webhookUrl": "http://localhost:3001/webhooks/a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890"
  }
}
```

**Usage:**
```bash
# Trigger the webhook
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/webhooks/a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890 \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"orderId": "123", "amount": 100}'
```

